  m_text: 'A nebula is a vast cloud of gas and dust in space. It is the raw material
    of the universe. Some nebulae are stellar

    nurseries where new stars are
    being born; others are the dramatic remnants of dying stars. The Milky Way galaxy

    itself
    is embedded within and contains thousands of nebulae, including the famous Orion
    Nebula, Eagle Nebula

    (Pillars of Creation), and Crab Nebula. Nebulae glow
    because nearby stars ionise the gas, causing it to emit light.'
